result.name: 同心泰國菜館

reviews.text: It is one of the oldest & most authentic Thai restaurants in the Kowloon City area, which is full of Thai shops & restaurants anyway. Dishes in general are tasty although prices have gone up quite a bit over the years, but still reasonable. Just don't expect a romantic dinner as it is just a crowded & cheerful eatery.
Mango sticky rice was quite good. Their curry has special spice, very interesting. Overall alright, had couple of Thai food before, the other two on the next street are more popular for a reason.

Besides popular localized Thai dishes Ruamjai does authentic and good Thai food. Clientele includes quite a few Thai people. The place looks more like a cha chan teng than a restaurant which probably contributes to the inexpensive prices
Awesome Thai Food I even had
As yummy as usual, I've been it's fan for years. Truly recommend the curry crab, it's magnificent!

result.name: Ruamjai Thai Restaurant

reviews.text: 環境👍午餐😀👌

It is one of the oldest & most authentic Thai restaurants in the Kowloon City area, which is full of Thai shops & restaurants anyway. Dishes in general are tasty although prices have gone up quite a bit over the years, but still reasonable. Just don't expect a romantic dinner as it is just a crowded & cheerful eatery.
價錢合理, 好食(串燒, 炒椰菜苗最好食) (食過幾間九龍城泰菜, 呢間最好食), 環境有如去了泰國的平民餐廳! 一定會再黎
好食 價廉 唯一缺點要300元才可用信用卡
味道唔錯，烏頭黑鯽好味
